This paper deals with planning and decision-making for robots, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of Markov Decision Processes (MDPs) and Linear Temporal Logic (LTL) also suggests a focus on Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also introduces a neural sequence-to-sequence model, indicating a possible focus on Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with hierarchical abstractions, which suggests a focus on Programming Languages (cs.PL).
